   "id": "104cb60a-31d6-47e7-9858-339ebe83f859",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here’s how powers of 10 correspond to their representation on an abacus, shown in a table:\n",
    "\n",
    "| **Power of 10** | **Value**           | **Chinese Character** | **Pinyin**    | **Abacus Column**      |\n",
    "|------------------|---------------------|------------------------|---------------|-------------------------|\n",
    "| $10^0$         | 1                   | 一                     | yī            | Rightmost column       |\n",
    "| $10^1$         | 10                  | 十                     | shí           | 2nd column from right  |\n",
    "| $10^2$         | 100                 | 百                     | bǎi           | 3rd column from right  |\n",
    "| $10^3$         | 1,000               | 千                     | qiān          | 4th column from right  |\n",
    "| $10^4$         | 10,000              | 万                     | wàn           | 5th column from right  |\n",
    "| $10^5$         | 100,000             | 十万                   | shíwàn        | 6th column from right  |\n",
    "| $10^6$         | 1,000,000           | 百万                   | bǎiwàn        | 7th column from right  |\n",
    "| $10^7$         | 10,000,000          | 千万                   | qiānwàn       | 8th column from right  |\n",
    "| $10^8$         | 100,000,000         | 亿                     | yì            | 9th column from right  |\n",
    "| $10^9$         | 1,000,000,000       | 十亿                   | shíyì         | 10th column from right |\n",
    "| $10^{10}$      | 10,000,000,000      | 百亿                   | bǎiyì         | 11th column from right |\n",
    "| $10^{11}$      | 100,000,000,000     | 千亿                   | qiānyì        | 12th column from right |\n",
    "| $10^{12}$      | 1,000,000,000,000   | 兆                     | zhào          | 13th column from right |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Notes:\n",
    "- Each **column on the abacus** corresponds to one of these powers of 10.\n",
    "- Numbers on the abacus are represented by summing up bead values in their respective columns, based on the position they represent."
   ]
  },
